(4461, 'Quality Management Systems', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'breadcrumb', 'first-iso'),
(4462, '<p>ONSITES High School is a globally accessible online U.S. high school based in Florida. Students enroll from multiple countries, study across different time zones, and progress through diploma programs within a flexible digital learning environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Delivering effective online education for an international student body requires clearly defined institutional processes. ISO 9001:2015 provides the quality management framework that ONSITES High School uses to organize, maintain, and continuously improve these processes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Institutional Process Management at ONSITES High School</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ISO 9001:2015 is the world&rsquo;s most widely adopted quality management standard, applied by over one million organizations across more than 170 countries. For ONSITES High School, it provides the framework for defining and documenting the institutional processes that keep online education reliable for every student, regardless of location.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How ONSITES High School Structures Academic Administration</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Running an online school for students across multiple countries means every core process must work the same way every time. At ONSITES High School, that requires well-defined procedures from the moment a student enrolls to the moment they receive their diploma.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Core school operations include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>enrollment and onboarding procedures for international students</li>\r\n	<li>course registration within diploma tracks</li>\r\n	<li>grading and assessment procedures across all courses</li>\r\n	<li>academic record administration and credit tracking</li>\r\n	<li>official transcript generation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Documented workflows guide how students enroll, complete coursework, and receive official academic records. The operational structure remains consistent across the entire learning environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What Structured Academic Processes Mean for Students and Families</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well-defined institutional procedures give students and families a clear picture of what to expect throughout the program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students and families benefit from:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>predictable enrollment and course registration steps</li>\r\n	<li>transparent grading policies with clear assessment criteria</li>\r\n	<li>progress records accessible to students and parents</li>\r\n	<li>uniform institutional standards applied across the global student body</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These standards apply to every student in the Standard, Honors, and ACCEL diploma tracks. Families can rely on a common baseline of transparency from enrollment through graduation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Academic Record Management at ONSITES High School</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every completed course and earned credit is recorded as part of the school&rsquo;s quality management system. ONSITES High School manages academic documentation through controlled practices aligned with ISO 9001:2015, emphasizing accuracy and consistency throughout.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Academic record administration includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>registering every course (core, elective, AP, CTE, CLEP, and prep programs) with an official Florida Department of Education course code</li>\r\n	<li>tracking completed coursework and earned credits within the school&rsquo;s institutional systems</li>\r\n	<li>generating official digital transcripts that document diploma progress</li>\r\n	<li>maintaining standardized documentation procedures across all diploma tracks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through these practices, student academic records remain accurate, verifiable, and aligned with recognized U.S. education standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Continuous Review of Institutional Operations</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ISO 9001:2015 is built around continual improvement. The standard calls for regular review of operational procedures and refinement where needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ONSITES High School regularly evaluates its institutional processes, including:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>enrollment workflows and admission procedures</li>\r\n	<li>course administration and grading processes</li>\r\n	<li>academic record management systems</li>\r\n	<li>student support and communication procedures</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through these evaluations, ONSITES High School refines its operations over time, ensuring that the quality framework that welcomed the first student continues to serve every student that follows.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'content', 'first-iso'),
