INSERT INTO `texts` (`id`, `text_en`, `text_de`, `text_bg`, `text_es`, `text_ru`, `editor`, `title`, `slug`) VALUES
(4473, '<p>Since 1983, the President&rsquo;s Education Awards Program (PEAP) has recognized academic achievement in U.S. schools on behalf of the President of the United States and the U.S. Secretary of Education. ONSITES High School participates in this program, administering three award categories under the program that together recognize the full range of what students can accomplish: sustained academic excellence, meaningful educational growth, and the qualities of character that define a student beyond any transcript.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Each award carries a certificate signed by the President of the United States and the U.S. Secretary of Education, administered nationally through the National Association of Secondary School Principals (NASSP). This distinction is relevant for international students and families: these are not internal school certificates or privately issued honors. They belong to a structured federal recognition program with a shared framework applied consistently across participating schools.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All enrolled students are eligible for consideration regardless of enrollment package. Because ONSITES High School operates on a rolling enrollment calendar with 12-month round schooling, students graduate at different points in the year rather than in a single annual cohort. Awards are presented at graduation, tying each student&rsquo;s recognition to their own academic milestone. Final decisions rest with the Head of School and are applied consistently across all candidates using the criteria for each award.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participation in the President&rsquo;s Education Awards Program is one of the ways ONSITES High School defines one element of the school&rsquo;s academic positioning: that academic achievement takes more than one form, and that every form is worth naming.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'intro', 'awards'),
(4474, '<h3><strong>President&#39;s Award for Educational Excellence</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The President&rsquo;s Award for Educational Excellence recognizes consistent, high-level academic performance in the classroom. To be eligible, a student must maintain a GPA of at least 3.5 on the standard U.S. 4.0 scale, on which 4.0 represents the highest possible score. GPA alone is not sufficient: candidates must also satisfy one of two additional criteria under the PEAP framework.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first option is achievement at or above the 85th percentile in mathematics or reading on a recognized standardized assessment. The second is a formal teacher recommendation attesting to the student&rsquo;s academic performance. Either satisfies the requirement alongside the GPA baseline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Recipients receive a certificate signed by the President of the United States and the U.S. Secretary of Education.</p>\r\n</div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'first-award', 'awards'),
(4475, '<h3><strong>President&#39;s Award for Educational Achievement</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>The Achievement Award is not a secondary recognition. The President&rsquo;s Education Awards Program describes it in explicit terms as honoring a very different type of academic achievement, and that framing is intentional. This award is designed for students who demonstrate outstanding growth, unusual commitment to learning, or exceptional effort in the face of real obstacles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At ONSITES High School, candidates for this award are considered on the basis of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Significant academic growth over time, even where overall performance did not reach the Excellence threshold</li>\r\n	<li>Unusual commitment to learning demonstrated despite personal, health-related, or external challenges</li>\r\n	<li>Strong academic performance that would have met Excellence criteria, but was prevented by illness, personal crisis, or circumstances outside the student&rsquo;s control despite genuine effort</li>\r\n	<li>Outstanding improvement or high achievement in specific subjects</li>\r\n	<li>Distinction in disciplines such as the arts or music</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The measure for this award is not whether a student reached a statistical threshold. It is whether they gave their best, and what that effort produced.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Recipients receive a certificate signed by the President of the United States and the U.S. Secretary of Education.</p>\r\n</div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'second-award', 'awards'),
(4476, '<h3><strong>American Citizenship Award</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Academic performance is one measure of what a student contributes. The American Citizenship Award recognizes another: the character, civic responsibility, and positive presence a student brings to the school community. There are no GPA requirements and no standardized test benchmarks. Any enrolled student at any grade level is eligible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ONSITES High School awards this recognition to students who demonstrate respect for peers and community, integrity and ethical conduct in their academic work, a positive contribution to the school environment, and a genuine sense of civic responsibility. Selection rests with the Head of School, applied consistently and fairly across all enrolled students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'third-award', 'awards'),
(4477, 'Credit Recovery', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'breadcrumb', 'credit-recovery'),
(4478, '<p>Credit recovery is designed for students who could not complete a course for reasons that may lie at their school, in their personal lives, or in the world around them. ONSITES High School offers credit recovery, operating in compliance with applicable state education requirements. Students complete the required course through the school, receive an official digital transcript, and submit it to their home school for credit acceptance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What Credit Recovery at ONSITES High School Is and Who It Serves</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A credit recovery course is a formal academic course taught to the same standard as any other, leading to the same recognized credit. At ONSITES High School, credit recovery is available as an external service to students currently enrolled at other schools worldwide: students who previously attempted a course but were unable to finish or pass it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students do not transfer their enrollment or leave their home school. They take the specific course or courses they need through the school, complete the work, and receive an official ONSITES High School digital transcript reflecting the earned credit. That transcript transmitted directly to the home school for credit acceptance onto the student&#39;s record.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Circumstances That Bring Students to ONSITES High School for Credit Recovery</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ONSITES High School credit recovery is structured for students affected by defined academic or external constraints, not for students who simply did not apply themselves. The circumstances that qualify are varied, and many are entirely outside the student&#39;s control.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Institutional and scheduling circumstances:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Course cancelled mid-year by the home school</li>\r\n	<li>Teacher departure or prolonged absence without adequate replacement</li>\r\n	<li>Curriculum gaps or inadequate instruction leaving the student underprepared for assessment</li>\r\n	<li>Required subject not offered at the student&#39;s current school</li>\r\n	<li>Timetable conflict preventing the student from completing a required course</li>\r\n	<li>School or program closure</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Personal and life circumstances:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Extended illness or medical treatment requiring extended absence</li>\r\n	<li>Family relocation or displacement, including as a result of civil disruption</li>\r\n	<li>Caring responsibilities for a family member</li>\r\n	<li>Bereavement or family emergency</li>\r\n	<li>Mental health challenges requiring time away from regular schooling</li>\r\n	<li>Competitive athletics, performing arts, or professional training with sustained travel demands</li>\r\n	<li>Large-scale disruptions such as pandemics or civil instability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Credit recovery does not inherently imply academic inability. Each of these circumstances is recognized by ONSITES High School as a legitimate reason to seek a structured pathway to course completion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How Credit Recovery Works at ONSITES High School</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Authorization before enrollment. Before a student can enroll, ONSITES High School requires a signed authorization from the home school, issued by the student&#39;s school counselor, principal, or another authorized school official, confirming that the completed credit will be accepted onto the student&#39;s home school record.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This step protects the student. It removes any ambiguity about whether the recovered credit will count before the student has invested time and money in the course. ONSITES High School can provide course syllabi and official course documentation upon request to support the home school&#39;s review.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior attempt. Credit recovery at ONSITES High School applies to courses a student has previously attempted and not completed or passed. As part of their application, students submit a transcript or grade report from the home school confirming prior enrollment and non-completion. A course the student has never enrolled in is not eligible under this program; that would be a standard course enrollment rather than a recovery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Course availability. Credit recovery is available across the full ONSITES High School course catalog. Every course carries an official Florida Department of Education (FLDOE) course code, formally registering the subject, credit value, and course type within Florida&#39;s academic system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Course delivery. Every credit recovery course is fully online and self-paced, accessible from any country and any time zone. Enrollment is rolling, with no fixed start dates. Students work through the course on their own schedule with access to certified ONSITES educators throughout.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Course fee. ONSITES High School prices credit recovery at the course&#39;s standard rate:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Standard module course: $490</li>\r\n	<li>Honors course: $590</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Students who previously attempted a standard-level course recover at $490; those who attempted an honors-level course recover at $590. No additional registration fee applies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After completion. Students who pass the course receive an official ONSITES High School digital transcript reflecting the completed course, the earned credit value, and the grade. The school sends this transcript directly to the home school on file. The decision to apply that credit to the student&#39;s home school record rests with the receiving institution, and the authorization obtained before enrollment is what makes that acceptance straightforward.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why Home Schools Accept the ONSITES High School Transcript</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When a home school considers whether to accept a credit from an external provider, the first question is institutional standing. ONSITES High School is a Florida-licensed online high school operating in compliance with Florida Department of Education requirements under official school code 5115. That recognition places the school within Florida&#39;s regulated educational framework: not a private certificate issuer, but a state-recognized institution accountable to Florida&#39;s academic and operational standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every course in the ONSITES High School curriculum carries an official FLDOE course code, formally registering the subject, credit value, and course type within Florida&#39;s education system. When a home school receives an ONSITES High School transcript, it receives a record tied to a named, verifiable state system. That is the basis on which home schools have grounds to accept externally completed credits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Credit recovery at ONSITES High School is open to students enrolled at formally recognized schools worldwide. The student&#39;s home institution must be officially recognized by the relevant national or regional education authority in their country; there is no geographic restriction beyond that requirement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Applying for Credit Recovery at ONSITES High School</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applications are submitted through the ONSITES High School Admissions section. Students and families complete the online application form, which includes fields for the course to be recovered, the home school&#39;s contact details for authorization purposes, and the supporting documentation confirming prior enrollment and non-completion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before applying, students should have three things ready:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The name of the course to be recovered</li>\r\n	<li>A transcript or grade report from the home school confirming the prior attempt</li>\r\n	<li>Confirmation from the home school official who will sign the authorization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having these prepared before first contact shortens the path from application to enrollment.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 'content', 'credit-recovery'),
(4485, 'Stand Out With a US High School Diploma Boosting Your Local Graduation.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'subheading', 'credit-transfer'),
